  <bioghist id="aspace_5ee29901e13b83005be70e95ccc1d1e5">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Professor Emeritus in the Dept. of Design and Environmental Analysis, Cornell University.</p><p> Sims received a Bachelor of Architecture degree from the University of New Mexico in 1963, a Masters in Architecture degree from the University of Pennsylvania in 1965 and a PhD from MIT in 1974.</p><p> Sims was active in facility management education since his arrival at Cornell in 1980 and was co-director of the International Workplace Studies Program.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_5096f3e758f2f8fdda8b2a87f917a6a4">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Correspondence, publications, reports, course material, and subject files relating to Sims' work in facility management and designing workplaces.</p>  </scopecontent>
